      <Description>This dataset contains differential fluxes of CNO ions from 8 energy channels, omni-directional observed by the 
        IIMS detector heads of the Research with Adaptive Particle Imaging Detectors (RAPID) instrument onboard Cluster C3.
        
        The RAPID spectrometer for the Cluster mission is an advanced particle detector for the analysis of suprathermal plasma distributions 
        in the energy range from 39-400 keV for electrons, 28-1500 keV (4000 keV) for hydrogen, and 10 keV/nuc - 1500 keV (4000 keV) 
        for heavier ions.
        
        The middle ion detector head failed early in the Mission. The ion time-of-flight system failed December 1, 2009; no ion measurements are possible afterwards.
        Since about 2007, the efficiencies of the electron detectors have steadily decayed, the effect being strongest for those perpendicular
        to the spin axis (so-called donut effect). Correction factors are being applied as best as can be determined, but must be viewed with caution.
      </Description>
